<subSubSection id="1C8A6552A521890C8CE74DD88961347A" pageId="63" pageNumber="336" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="542F36D9A521890C8CE74DD88961347A" blockId="63.[151,756,1257,1377]" pageId="63" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA521890C8CE74DD888F2341A" bold="true" box="[151,254,1257,1281]" pageId="63" pageNumber="336">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA521890C8D624DDB8972341A" authorityName="GR Florina" baseAuthorityName="MORAWITZ" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[274,382,1257,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpinus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA521890C8D624DDB8972341A" box="[274,382,1257,1281]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="336">H. alpinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a European species, which according to DATHE et al. (2016) is found on mountain locations, preferably at altitudes between 
<quantity id="93689B3CA521890C8E004C188AB3345A" box="[624,703,1321,1345]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="63" pageNumber="336" unit="m" value="1000.0">1000 m</quantity>
and 
<quantity id="93689B3CA521890C8CE74C7888EA347A" box="[151,230,1353,1377]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="63" pageNumber="336" unit="m" value="2100.0">2100 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="CCAB2A5CA521890C8C844C78896E347A" box="[244,354,1353,1377]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="68.[211,244,1429,1451]" captionTargetBox="[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetId="figure-259@68.[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="Fig. 17: Distribution map of rarely recorded Hylaeus species in Turkey: species collected in only one (1-12) or two (II-X)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742935/files/figure.png" pageId="63" pageNumber="336">Fig. 17.10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1C8A6552A521890C8CE74CB88A2E373A" pageId="63" pageNumber="336" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="542F36D9A521890C8CE74CB88A2E373A" blockId="63.[151,756,1417,1570]" pageId="63" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA521890C8CE74CB8892B34BA" bold="true" box="[151,295,1417,1441]" pageId="63" pageNumber="336">Distribution:</emphasis>
Pyrenees, Alps (up to 
<quantity id="93689B3CA521890C8E304CB88A9D34BA" box="[576,657,1417,1441]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="63" pageNumber="336" unit="m" value="1900.0">1900 m</quantity>
), Tatras, Balkans, Northern 
<collectingCountry id="2C877649A521890C8D1E4C9889B434DA" box="[366,440,1449,1473]" name="Greece" pageId="63" pageNumber="336">Greece</collectingCountry>
(Varnous, Pindos). 
<bibRefCitation id="30014B28A521890C8EED4C98897034FA" author="ASCHER, J. S. &amp; PICKERING, J." pageId="63" pageNumber="336" refId="ref67970" refString="ASCHER, J. S. &amp; PICKERING, J. 2019: Discover Life - Bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). - Available from: http: // discoverlife. org / mp / 20 q? search = Apoidea (last accessed 12 June 2019)." type="url" year="2019">ASCHER &amp; PICKERING (2019)</bibRefCitation>
in “Discover Life” state that this species occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="2C877649A521890C8D204CD88997371A" box="[336,411,1513,1537]" name="Turkey" pageId="63" pageNumber="336">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, but the dots on their maps refer only to the country, not to a location.
</paragraph>
